{"key":"processedPost-17097840","value":{"id":17097840,"first":17097828,"last":17097891,"when":1351178220,"utime":"10/25/12 06:17 PM","content":"Smaller jars are better for brf, and make sure the jar is as wide as it is tall. Tall, skinny jars usually don't colonize fully. 250ml is best, but the slightly larger is OK as long as it meets the above.<br /><br />Don't attempt to mix single jar amounts.&nbsp; Mix the brown rice flour and vermiculite in a large bowl as demonstrated in the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/BRF-Pf-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">brf tek videos</a>, and then fill the jars.<br />RR","title":"Re: substrate measurements","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}